MQA.BaseTile

Base Tile class.  Constructs a new MQA.BaseTile object.

Parameters

parent(object) DIV element to contain the tile
left(int) Left position in XY coordinates of the upper left corner of the tile
top(int) Top position in XY coordinates of the upper left corner of the tile.
gridColumn(int) The column number of the tile.
gridRow(int) The row number of the tile.
scale(int) The map scale of the tile.
zoom(int) The zoom level of the tile.
size(int) The length in pixels of each side of the tile.
opacity(float) The opacity of the tile (0 - 1)

Note

This object is used to create custom tiles.  It is not to be instantiated directly.

Tiles are assumed to be square.

updateTile

Sets the loading tile image to the tile.

Parameters

left(int) The X coordinate of the upper left corner of the tile in pixels.
top(int) The Y coordinate of the upper left corner of the tile in pixels.
gridColumn(int) The column on the map the image is to be taken from to load the tile.
gridRow(int) The row on the map the image is to be taken from to load the tile.
scale(int) The current scale of the map.
zoom(int) The current zoom level of the map.

MQA.BaseTileLayer

Tile Layer class Constructs a new MQA.TileLayer object

Parameters

map(MQA.TileMap) The tiled map to hold the tile layer object.
tileLayerId(string) The user-defined DOM Id of this tile layer.
tileClass(MQA.BaseTile) The tile object to use for this tile layer options
bounds(MQA.RectLL) The bounds where the tile layer will show.
minZoom(int) The minimum zoom level for this tile layer to be visible.
maxZoom(int) The maximum zoom level for this tile layer to be visible.
opacity(float) The opacity of the tile layer (0 - 1).
zindex(int) The zIndex of the tile layer.
copyright(MQA.Copyright) The copyright object to attach to the tile layer.

Extends

MQA.Base

Properties

These properties can be manipulated via the MQA.Base.setValue, MQA.Base.setValues, and MQA.Base.getValue functions.
